The "write EPIPE" error typically occurs when the remote server has terminated the connection before the request could be fully processed. This could be due to various reasons such as network congestion, timeouts, or server issues.

To resolve this error, you can try the following:

1. Increase the timeout value for your request using the "timeout" option. For example:

```
request({
    url: 'https://example.com',
    timeout: 5000 // set timeout to 5 seconds
}, function (error, response, body) {
  // handle response
});
```

2. Check if the specified URL is valid and the remote server is up and running.

3. Try sending the request again after a few seconds or minutes.

If none of these solutions work, you may need to investigate further to identify the root cause of the issue.

