2. If you are behind a proxy, you can try setting the `httpsAgent` and `httpAgent` configuration options to use your proxy server.

```
const https = require('https');
const http = require('http');

axios({
   url: 'https://example.com',
   httpsAgent: new https.Agent({ rejectUnauthorized: false, proxy: 'http://my-proxy-server:8080' }),
   httpAgent: new http.Agent({ rejectUnauthorized: false, proxy: 'http://my-proxy-server:8080' }),
}).then(response => {
   // handle the response
}).catch(error => {
   // handle the error
})
```

3. Try disabling the SSL certificate verification by setting the `rejectUnauthorized` configuration option to false:

```
